column1: # Name: Freedom of the Press (FOTP) score by Freedom House

# Definition: The index assesses the degree of print, broadcast, and internet freedom in every country in the world, analyzing the events of each calendar year. It provides numerical rankings and scores (as well as categorisations of each country's media as "Free," "Partly Free," or "Not Free.")
# Data from the No Ceilings project: http://noceilings.org
# For more about the data, please visit http://noceilings.org/data
